\begin{quote}
In physics we study the relationships between measurements. These
measure-ments are expressed with reference to certain yardsticks, also
known as units of measurements. These yardsticks are not dened by some a
priori principle, rather they follow from a concatenation of historical
(and in hindsight often rather arbitrary) conventions.7
\end{quote}

