\begin{quote}
From these examples it should be clear that \textquotesingle adding
depth\textquotesingle{} to a diagram by stacking linear layers makes
little sense. Doing so tends to increase the number of weights while the
expressive power of the net does not increase.

Including rectiers, adding depth becomes much more meaningful, and more
complex (nonlinear) functional relationships can be created. A simple
example is shown on the right: a weighted linear sum feeding into a
rectier. This particular
\end{quote}
