sample \textbf{x}\emph{i} full knowledge of the partial
derivatives\emph{\uline{∂E}}(\emph{i})\emph{∂}\textbf{w}. The
backpropagation algorithm18 provides us with these partial derivatives
in just one single reverse sweep through the network. This is done by
rst computing the partial derivatives of the error
