Step 7: Implement stochastic gradient descent with backpropegation for
the architecture and training data selected. This step can be coded by
hand, or be implemented using an available deep-learning platform (e.g.
Keras.
\end{quote}

Step 8: Train for multiple epochs (multiple full passes through all
training

\begin{quote}
data).

Step 9: Critically analyse the results. Use the training errors and test
errors as function of the number of epochs of training to identify
under/overtraining.

Step 10: Repeat steps 6-9 as often as required.
\end{quote}

