example discussed in the previous section, demonstrate the essence of
temporal dierence learning. The idea applies in principle to any problem
where a t is sought to data that can be obtained from an iterative
process. In such regression applications, often a t more accurate than a
linear t is sought. This is where temporal dierence learning really
shines, as the technique is not limited to linear nets, but rather
combines well with deep feedforward nets. The same core idea can be used
for real-time control and optimisation of instable dynamical systems. An
example is discussed in the next section.
