\begin{quote}
These notes provide an introduction to state-of-the-art techniques in
machine learning.Where a trade-o between completeness and depth of
coverage was needed, preference was given to the latter. This ensured
that, despite the in-troductory nature of this text, advanced and
exciting topics such as deep con-volutional nets and reinforcement
learning via temporal dierence mechanisms could be included. The ip-side
however, is that many areas of machine learning had to be left out. Most
notably, the whole text is focused on regression prob-lems where we seek
a continuous function describing the data. Classication problems have
not been discussed.

Taking the current text as a starting point, the reader can seek broader
ML knowledge in various textbooks. Excellent more recent textbooks
include the books by Abu-Mostafa et al.32, and Murphy33To deepen
knowledge in feedforward nets and convolutional nets, the book by
Goodfellow et al.34 is recommended. For more info on reinforcement
learning the reader is referred to the second edition of the classical
work by Sutton and Barto.35\\
Also worth noting are some recent review papers in the scientic
literature that follow an approach similar to the current text, with the
aiming to render

